dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_247  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: MADD/DENN was shown to function as KIF1 motor adapter. GTP-bound Rab3, which is a marker of synaptic vesicle transport vesicles (STVs), binds MADD which then allows KIF1-dependent transport of Rab3-STVs. Expression of a dominant negative MADD (death domain) blocks binding of Rab3-STVs to KIF1. Reduced Rab3-STVs in distal axons and a decrease in anterograde-moving Rab3-STVs in proximal axons were observed in neurons expressing dominant negative MADD/DENN or miRNA against MADD/DENN. Taken together, these results indicates that movement of STVs to presynaptic sites via KIF1 motors are dependent on MADD/DENN.\n\n29/3/2017 Pim\n- Rab3A is a known SV protein and in this paper and PMID:7539720 considered as a marker of precursor synaptic vesicles (see discussion with expert in feedback section). Effects on Rab3A lcoalization are therefore annotated against transport of synaptic vesicles.. Experimental description: Tissue: mouse\nFrom Materials and Methods \"Rab3 isoforms and DENN/MADD cDNA were amplified by PCR from RIKEN FANTOM mouse clones (Dnaform) and from KIAA0358 clone (Kazusa DNA Institute), respectively.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_247" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

